Add method to calculate if a player's pick is unique and display it
My wife wrote all this code - you can tell now that we are embedding SQL statements and not using SQLAlachemy. And I'm so grateful because it probably would have taken me days if not weeks to do what she just did in a few hours. And a new column displays when a player views their picks on their account page showing if a pick is unique.

Wildcard picks were missing the column showing 25 points for each correct Wildcard pick

Fix change picks for pick type 8
Interceptions had a pick type of 4 when they SHOULD be pick type 8. Fixed.

Fix broken queries
All of the individual player picks had a bad copy / paste where the correct pick type was not updated. All update queries were missing a filter by year so it was updating all rows for the pool player's pick including past seasons. (Oops!)

Update copy on completed pick page

Fix incorrect change query / filters for individual stats

Update AFC East Winner Pick and update
Team place picks are having their timestamp updated even when not being changed - this is due to the way the query was written. Wrote new query using for loop and is now working as expected. Need to update all the other picks.
